U.S. Requests Public Comment to Improve Insurance Regulation

-- B y   A n d r e w   F r y e
-- 
2011-10-17T18:49:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/u-s-requests-public-comment-to-improve-insurance-regulation.html
The U.S. Treasury Department’s
Federal Insurance Office said it is seeking comments from the
public in its push to “modernize and improve” regulation of
the industry it monitors.  The office requested comments “from policyholders,
experts, consumer groups, state insurance regulators, insurance
industry representatives and all other interested parties,”
Treasury said today in a  statement .  To contact the reporters on this story:
Andrew Frye in New York at 
 afrye@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  